Button, doesn't restore down state after pressed mouse make rollout & rollin.
There is small obscurity based on `buttonRect` and `MAX_DRAG_DIST`, but afaik restore down state after rollout & rollin is a good practice.

I use this code addition in `Button#onTouch()` to add functionality (based on prev `else if` block)

``` as3
...
else if (touch.phase == TouchPhase.MOVED && state == ButtonState.UP)
{
    var buttonRect:Rectangle = getBounds(stage);
    if (touch.globalX > buttonRect.x &&
        touch.globalY > buttonRect.y &&
        touch.globalX < buttonRect.x + buttonRect.width &&
        touch.globalY < buttonRect.y + buttonRect.height)
    {
        state = ButtonState.DOWN;
    }
}
...
```

We have a small problem when upgrading to the newest Starling
We have a single sprite ATF spritesheet, with the SubTexture named the same as the file name.
And I ended up seeing the ATF texture with the wrong size (showing as the size of the file instead of the size of the sub texture)
The atf file is loaded into the mTextures and then mTextureAtlas when the xml is processed but without removing from mTextures.

In an older version of AssetManager we have
addTextureAtlas(name, new TextureAtlas(texture, xml));
removeTexture(name, false);

In the newer version of AssetManager there's only
addTextureAtlas(name, new TextureAtlas(texture, xml));

I think that might be the issue. Is it possible to add that line back in?

